> One more thing..... when is it most neccessary to use a Chunky display
> rather than a Planar display???? which display would be quicker for a 3d
> space game that will use textured polygons??
> 
textured polygons in general require chunky display - nowadays c2p 
routines are done in almost copymem speed with 68030@50Mhz, so 
overhead is not really that big. The other advantage is that you can 
directly copy the chunky buffer into a gfx card's videoRAM and 
provided you open your screens properly, use any type of display.

however there was this demo of AlienF1 that claimed to be doing 
bitplane-based tmapping. It was pretty fast, but it didn't look very 
good. 


