> WriteList(&Txt$(0))
> 
> But how can I access anything but the first element of the string 
> array.  I'm using Peek but assembler would be good as an alternative?

 The structure of a blitz string is (hopefully):
	length.w
	*strptr.b

 The address of  a string (&Txt$(0)) would give you the address of 
the *strptr.b for that string. An array of strings could then be 
accessed by getting the base of the array (base.l = &Txt$(0)) 
then using a$=peek$(peek.l(base + 6 * index)) where 6 is the size of 
the structure (see above) and index is the string you want to access.

 Warning: there is a high possibility that this could all be 
b*llocks.


