You should get the id just using ASLScreenRequest, like this

WBStartup

NEWTYPE .scrinfo
  id.l
  width.l
  height.l
  dept.w
  overscan.w
  autoscrol.w
  bmapwidth.l
  bmapheight.l
End NEWTYPE

FindScreen 0

*sc.scrinfo=3DASLScreenRequest(0)

Nprint *sc\id

vwait 4
mousewait
end

