Mmmm........... not really, have you done something like "WbToScreen 0" or
something? apart from that, I can't really help you. I do know however, that a
lot of commands that come with Blitz are pretty mugh faulty. For example,
WBWidth, and WBHeight return crap results on a Gfx Card. Also, FastFree and
ChipFree are sometimes faulty, especially Fastfree.

 
> Is there a command that DOES give the correct result?

Nope, but u can do this:

scr.l=Addr Screen(0)
pubscr.l=Peek.l(scr)

width=Peek.w(pubscr+12)
height=Peek.w(pubscr+14)

So there you go!


