playing time in VBlanks so I can set a timer to know when the sound is done.  

The sound objects contain the information for the period (playing speed) of a
sound, and it's length, and I am sure there is a way to determine the playing
time from this.  However, I am not very good with math, and I am not able to
determine this relationship.  I am attaching a small test code that will load
a sample, give it's period & length, then let you set the waiting time by
trial & error.
